[[sn:Senzan Seven Lucky Gods Pilgrimage]] [[ja:泉山七福神巡り]]

'''Senzan Seven Lucky Gods Pilgrimage''' (泉山七福神巡り, せんざんしちふくじんめぐり) is an event in which pilgrims visit seven sub-temples<ref>When extras are included, the total number becomes nine. The main hall of [[:en:Sennyū-ji|Sennyūji]] is also counted as an extra.</ref> located within the mountain precincts of [[:en:Sennyū-ji|Sennyū-ji]] in [[:en:Kyoto Prefecture|Kyoto Prefecture]] [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto City]] [[:en:Higashiyama-ku, Kyoto|Higashiyama Ward]]. It is held annually on the second [[:en:Monday|Monday]] of [[:en:January|January]] ([[:en:Coming of Age Day|Coming of Age Day]]) as a pilgrimage of the [[:en:Seven Lucky Gods|Seven Lucky Gods]].<ref>[http://www.mitera.org/7huku.php Official site of Sennyūji – Senzan Seven Lucky Gods Pilgrimage]</ref><ref>Until [[:en:1999|1999]] ([[:en:Heisei era|Heisei]]11), the event was held annually on [[:en:January 15|January 15]], similar to Coming of Age Day.</ref>
== Overview == The belief in the Seven Lucky Gods is said to have originated in Kyoto during the [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi Period]], gradually spreading throughout Japan. It is believed that a New Year visit to the shrines brings good fortune. The Senzan Seven Lucky Gods Pilgrimage has been held every year on Coming of Age Day since [[:en:1951|1951]] ([[:en:Shōwa era|Showa]]26), and it is regarded as a grand New Year tradition that grows more elaborate each year.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20161228215616/http://www.mitera.org/event.php Official Sennyūji site – Annual Events] (Archived as of December 28, 2016 from the [[:en:Internet Archive|Archive]])</ref>
